Capturing and Analyzing Wi-Fi Deauthentication Frames using NodeMCU and Monitor Mode
📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates the generation, transmission, capture, and analysis of IEEE 802.11 deauthentication management frames within a controlled laboratory environment. The objective is to study wireless management frame vulnerabilities and understand how deauthentication attacks operate at the protocol level.

The system uses a NodeMCU ESP8266 microcontroller for packet injection and a monitor mode-enabled wireless adapter to capture raw Wi-Fi traffic. Captured packets are analyzed using Wireshark to inspect frame subtype, MAC addresses, and reason codes.

⚠️ This project is developed strictly for educational and research purposes in an authorized and isolated test environment.

🎯 Objectives

Study IEEE 802.11 management frame structure

Generate deauthentication frames using ESP8266

Capture wireless packets in monitor mode

Analyze deauthentication frame fields in Wireshark

Understand vulnerabilities in unprotected management frames

Highlight the importance of WPA3 and IEEE 802.11w

