⚙️ Installation & Setup
1️⃣ Install Kali Linux

Install Kali Linux as the primary penetration testing environment.

2️⃣ Install Arduino IDE

Download from:
https://www.arduino.cc/en/software

Add ESP8266 board manager URL:

https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SpacehuhnTech/arduino/main/package_spacehuhn_index.json
3️⃣ Flash ESP8266 Deauther Firmware

Repository:
https://github.com/SpacehuhnTech/esp8266_deauther

Steps:

Open firmware in Arduino IDE

Select NodeMCU ESP8266 board

Choose correct COM port

Upload firmware

Confirm hotspot named “pwned”

4️⃣ Install RTL8821AU Driver

Repository:
https://github.com/morrownr/8821au-20210708

git clone https://github.com/morrownr/8821au-20210708.git
cd 8821au-20210708
sudo ./install-driver.sh
5️⃣ Enable Monitor Mode

Repository:
https://github.com/morrownr/Monitor_Mode

sudo ./start-mon.sh wlan0

Verify:

iwconfig

Interface should change to wlan0mon.

6️⃣ Capture Packets using Wireshark

Launch:

wireshark

Select wlan0mon

Filter deauthentication frames:

wlan.fc.type_subtype == 0x0c
🧪 Experimental Procedure

Connect test device to NodeMCU hotspot.

Access web interface at 192.168.4.1.

